{"author":{"id":"cc8322a500b8739c77faac347808f6026d9ccb7880d0aaa7ad76754163cd7fdb"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"h8s/iqBpc/wzAnvpd4qGBVjua9s=","kind":"plan","title":"Slice 6b — Retier Implementation Plan"},{"type":3,"timestamp":1782568927,"nonce":"sGOdZOuMx1KB1d+GfhtJg5HGfws=","body":"# Slice 6b — Retier Implementation Plan\n\n\u003e **For agentic workers:** REQUIRED SUB-SKILL: Use superpowers:subagent-driven-development (recommended) or superpowers:executing-plans to implement this plan task-by-task. Steps use checkbox (`- [ ]`) syntax for tracking.\n\n**Goal:** Let an entry change visibility tier while keeping its identity — `kref retier`/`promote`/`share`/`private` — gated so a promotion to shared can't expose a secret and a post-push demote warns honestly.\n\n**Architecture:** `Store.Retier` is the capability core. The move is **read the entry's ops from its current tier → build a fresh entity in the target tier (append every op + a `retier` provenance op) → `Commit` → `dag.Remove` the old ref**. The id is preserved because git-bug op hashes exclude the Lamport clock (verified in source); the target tier re-clocks via the normal write path. The promote-to-shared **rescan is in the core** (unskippable, reuses 6a's `scanForPush`, fail-closed); the **confirmation prompt and cross-tier-link warning are CLI-layer UX** over exported store queries; **post-push demote warns-and-proceeds**. Reference: `docs/dev/specs/2026-06-20-unified-entry-model-design.md` §4.6 (\"6b build decisions\").\n\n**Tech Stack:** Go, git-bug entity/dag (`entry.Read`/`New`/`Append`/`Commit`, `dag.Remove`), gitleaks via the 6a `scanForPush`, 6a pushed-state (`pushedRef`/`RefExist`), ginkgo/gomega, Taskfile.\n\n---\n\n## Conventions for every task\n\n- **TDD loop:** failing test → run-fail → implement → run-pass → `gofmt -w` → commit.\n- **Test runner:** prefix Go commands with `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto`. `internal/store` + `cmd/kref` suites need `KREF_GITLEAKS=$(pwd)/bin/gitleaks`. `task test`/`task lint` are canonical.\n- **Ignore LSP \"GOTOOLCHAIN=local / No packages found / undefined\" diagnostics** — stale noise; trust `GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test`.\n- **Do NOT run `git stash`.** Stage files by name. Every commit ends with:\n  `Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 (1M context) \u003cnoreply@anthropic.com\u003e`\n- `internal/store` tests are `package store` (internal). The gitleaks fixture secret is `AKIALALEMEL33243OLIA`.\n\n## File structure\n\n| File | Change | Responsibility |\n|------|--------|----------------|\n| `internal/store/retier.go` | create | `Store.Retier`, `RetierBlockedError`, `Store.CrossTierLinks`, `Store.WasPushed`, `tierRank` |\n| `internal/store/retier_test.go` | create | round-trip, rescan gate, query tests |\n| `internal/entry/snapshot.go` | modify | extend the `Trigger` doc comment to include `retier` |\n| `cmd/kref/commands.go` | modify | `runRetier` + `confirmRetier` + `newRetierCmd`/`newPromoteCmd`/`newPrivateCmd` |\n| `cmd/kref/main.go` | modify | register the three commands in the lifecycle group |\n| `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` | modify | CLI tests |\n| `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md` | modify | docs |\n\n---\n\n## Task 1: `Store.Retier` core + round-trip verification (the make-or-break)\n\n**Files:** Create `internal/store/retier.go`, `internal/store/retier_test.go`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing round-trip test** — create `internal/store/retier_test.go`:\n\n```go\npackage store\n\nimport (\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/ginkgo/v2\"\n\t. \"github.com/onsi/gomega\"\n\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/entry\"\n)\n\nvar _ = Describe(\"Retier\", func() {\n\tIt(\"moves an entry to a new tier preserving id and all facets\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts, err := Init(dir, \"T\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = s.Close() })\n\n\t\tid, err := s.Add(entry.TierPersonal, \"spec\", \"Doc\", \"the body\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(s.AddLabel(id, \"area:auth\")).To(Succeed())\n\t\tExpect(s.SetStatus(id, \"accepted\")).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tExpect(s.Retier(id, entry.TierShared, \"tester\", \"human\")).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\t// Same id, now in shared, gone from personal, facets intact.\n\t\tsnap, err := s.Get(id)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(snap.ID).To(Equal(id))\n\t\tExpect(snap.Tier).To(Equal(\"shared\"))\n\t\tExpect(snap.Status).To(Equal(\"accepted\"))\n\t\tExpect(snap.Body).To(Equal(\"the body\"))\n\t\tExpect(snap.Labels).To(ContainElement(\"area:auth\"))\n\n\t\t_, err = entry.Read(s.repo, entry.TierPersonal, id)\n\t\tExpect(err).To(HaveOccurred()) // removed from the old tier\n\n\t\t// A retier provenance event was recorded.\n\t\ttriggers := make([]string, 0, len(snap.Provenance))\n\t\tfor _, p := range snap.Provenance {\n\t\t\ttriggers = append(triggers, p.Trigger)\n\t\t}\n\t\tExpect(triggers).To(ContainElement(\"retier\"))\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"is a no-op when the entry is already in the target tier\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts, err := Init(dir, \"T\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = s.Close() })\n\t\tid, err := s.Add(entry.TierPersonal, \"spec\", \"Doc\", \"b\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(s.Retier(id, entry.TierPersonal, \"tester\", \"human\")).To(Succeed())\n\t\tsnap, err := s.Get(id)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(snap.Tier).To(Equal(\"personal\"))\n\t})\n})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run, confirm FAIL** — `KREF_GITLEAKS=$(pwd)/bin/gitleaks GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/store/...` → FAIL (undefined: s.Retier).\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement** — create `internal/store/retier.go`:\n\n```go\npackage store\n\nimport (\n\t\"fmt\"\n\n\t\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity\"\n\t\"github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity/dag\"\n\n\t\"github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/entry\"\n)\n\n// Retier moves an entry to a new visibility tier, preserving its id. It reads the\n// entry's ops from its current tier, rebuilds the entity in the target tier (same\n// ops + a retier provenance event), commits, then removes the old ref. Op hashes\n// exclude the Lamport clock, so the id is stable; the target tier re-clocks via\n// the normal write path. Promoting to shared rescans for secrets, fail-closed.\nfunc (s *Store) Retier(id entity.Id, target entry.Tier, actor, actorKind string) error {\n\tvar cur entry.Tier\n\tvar e *entry.Entry\n\tfor _, t := range entry.AllTiers() {\n\t\tent, err := entry.Read(s.repo, t, id)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tif entity.IsErrNotFound(err) {\n\t\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"read %s in tier %s: %w\", id, t, err)\n\t\t}\n\t\tcur, e = t, ent\n\t\tbreak\n\t}\n\tif e == nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"entry %s not found\", id)\n\t}\n\tif cur == target {\n\t\treturn nil // already in the target tier\n\t}\n\t// Promote-to-shared secret gate (security; in core, unskippable by adapters).\n\tif target == entry.TierShared {\n\t\toffenders, err := s.scanForPush([]entity.Id{id})\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t}\n\t\tif len(offenders) \u003e 0 {\n\t\t\treturn \u0026RetierBlockedError{Offenders: offenders}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\t// Rebuild in the target tier: same ops (id preserved) + a retier event.\n\tnw := entry.New(target)\n\tfor _, op := range e.Operations() {\n\t\tnw.Append(op)\n\t}\n\tnw.Append(entry.NewRecordOrigin(s.author, actor, actorKind, \"\", \"retier\"))\n\tif err := nw.Commit(s.repo); err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"commit %s in tier %s: %w\", id, target, err)\n\t}\n\tif err := dag.Remove(entry.Definition(cur), s.repo, id); err != nil {\n\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"entry %s is now in both %s and %s; rerun retier to finish (remove old: %w)\", id, cur, target, err)\n\t}\n\treturn nil\n}\n\n// RetierBlockedError reports that a promote-to-shared was blocked by a secret.\n// Its message never contains the secret value.\ntype RetierBlockedError struct {\n\tOffenders []pushOffender\n}\n\nfunc (e *RetierBlockedError) Error() string {\n\tvar b strings.Builder\n\tb.WriteString(\"promote blocked: the entry carries a secret and cannot be shared.\\n\")\n\tb.WriteString(\"Offending entries (the secret value is not shown):\\n\")\n\tfor _, o := range e.Offenders {\n\t\tfmt.Fprintf(\u0026b, \"  - %s (%q): %s — %s\\n\", o.ID.String(), o.Title, o.Rule, o.Desc)\n\t}\n\tb.WriteString(\"Rotate the secret, `kref purge \u003cid\u003e --gc`, recreate the entry clean, then promote.\")\n\treturn b.String()\n}\n```\n\nNOTE: add `\"strings\"` to the import block (used by `RetierBlockedError.Error`). Final import set: `fmt`, `strings`, `github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity`, `github.com/git-bug/git-bug/entity/dag`, `github.com/riotbox/kref/internal/entry`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run, confirm PASS** — `KREF_GITLEAKS=$(pwd)/bin/gitleaks GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/store/...` → PASS. **If this fails because re-appending ops or committing the rebuilt entity errors, STOP and report — the move mechanism needs rethinking (fallback: CopyRef) and that is a design escalation, not a code tweak.**\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: gofmt + commit**\n\n```bash\ngofmt -w internal/store/retier.go internal/store/retier_test.go\ngit add internal/store/retier.go internal/store/retier_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(store): Retier moves an entry between tiers, id preserved\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 2: promote-to-shared rescan gate (verify fail-closed)\n\n**Files:** Modify `internal/store/retier_test.go` (append).\n\nThe gate is already implemented in `Store.Retier` (Task 1). This task adds the security tests that prove it.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing tests** — append inside `Describe(\"Retier\", ...)`:\n\n```go\n\tIt(\"blocks promotion to shared when the entry carries a secret (even in history)\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts, err := Init(dir, \"T\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = s.Close() })\n\t\tid, err := s.Add(entry.TierPersonal, \"spec\", \"Leaky\", \"AKIALALEMEL33243OLIA\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(s.Update(id, \"now clean\", \"\")).To(Succeed()) // secret only in history\n\n\t\terr = s.Retier(id, entry.TierShared, \"tester\", \"human\")\n\t\tExpect(err).To(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tvar rb *RetierBlockedError\n\t\tExpect(errors.As(err, \u0026rb)).To(BeTrue())\n\t\tExpect(rb.Offenders).To(HaveLen(1))\n\t\tExpect(err.Error()).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"AKIALALEMEL33243OLIA\"))\n\n\t\t// Still in personal — the blocked promote did not move it.\n\t\tsnap, err := s.Get(id)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(snap.Tier).To(Equal(\"personal\"))\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"allows promotion of a clean entry to shared\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts, err := Init(dir, \"T\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = s.Close() })\n\t\tid, err := s.Add(entry.TierPersonal, \"spec\", \"Fine\", \"just prose\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(s.Retier(id, entry.TierShared, \"tester\", \"human\")).To(Succeed())\n\t\tsnap, err := s.Get(id)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(snap.Tier).To(Equal(\"shared\"))\n\t})\n```\n\nAdd `\"errors\"` to the `retier_test.go` import block.\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run, confirm PASS** (the gate already exists from Task 1; these tests should pass immediately — they are regression protection for the security property).\n\n`KREF_GITLEAKS=$(pwd)/bin/gitleaks GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./internal/store/...` → PASS.\n\n(If the blocked-promote test FAILS — e.g. the entry moved despite the secret — that is a real security bug; STOP and fix `Store.Retier` before proceeding.)\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: gofmt + commit**\n\n```bash\ngofmt -w internal/store/retier_test.go\ngit add internal/store/retier_test.go\ngit commit -m \"test(store): promote-to-shared is fail-closed on secrets\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 3: soft-gate queries — `CrossTierLinks` + `WasPushed`\n\n**Files:** Modify `internal/store/retier.go` (append; add `entity` already imported), `internal/store/retier_test.go` (append).\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing tests** — append inside `Describe(\"Retier\", ...)`:\n\n```go\n\tIt(\"CrossTierLinks finds outgoing links to entries below the target tier\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts, err := Init(dir, \"T\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = s.Close() })\n\t\tfrom, err := s.Add(entry.TierPersonal, \"spec\", \"From\", \"b\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tpriv, err := s.Add(entry.TierPrivate, \"spec\", \"Secret dep\", \"b\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(s.AddLink(from, priv.String(), \"relates\")).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tdangling, err := s.CrossTierLinks(from, entry.TierShared)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(dangling).To(HaveLen(1))\n\t\tExpect(dangling[0].ID).To(Equal(priv))\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"WasPushed reports false before any push\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\ts, err := Init(dir, \"T\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tDeferCleanup(func() { _ = s.Close() })\n\t\tid, err := s.Add(entry.TierShared, \"spec\", \"X\", \"b\")\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tpushed, err := s.WasPushed(id)\n\t\tExpect(err).NotTo(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(pushed).To(BeFalse())\n\t})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run, confirm FAIL** — undefined `s.CrossTierLinks` / `s.WasPushed`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement** — append to `internal/store/retier.go`:\n\n```go\nfunc tierRank(t entry.Tier) int {\n\tswitch t {\n\tcase entry.TierPrivate:\n\t\treturn 0\n\tcase entry.TierPersonal:\n\t\treturn 1\n\tcase entry.TierShared:\n\t\treturn 2\n\tdefault:\n\t\treturn 3\n\t}\n}\n\n// CrossTierLinks returns the entry's outgoing links whose targets sit in a tier\n// below target — references teammates won't see after a promotion to target.\nfunc (s *Store) CrossTierLinks(id entity.Id, target entry.Tier) ([]entry.LinkRef, error) {\n\tsnap, err := s.Get(id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn nil, err\n\t}\n\tvar dangling []entry.LinkRef\n\tfor _, l := range snap.Links {\n\t\ttsnap, err := s.Get(entity.Id(l.To))\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\tcontinue // target not found (deleted/unknown) — skip\n\t\t}\n\t\tif tierRank(entry.Tier(tsnap.Tier)) \u003c tierRank(target) {\n\t\t\tdangling = append(dangling, entry.LinkRef{ID: entity.Id(l.To), Type: l.Type, Title: tsnap.Title})\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn dangling, nil\n}\n\n// WasPushed reports whether the entry was already pushed from any pushable tier\n// (a 6a kref-pushed mirror ref exists).\nfunc (s *Store) WasPushed(id entity.Id) (bool, error) {\n\tfor _, t := range entry.AllTiers() {\n\t\tif t == entry.TierPrivate {\n\t\t\tcontinue\n\t\t}\n\t\texist, err := s.repo.RefExist(pushedRef(t, id))\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn false, err\n\t\t}\n\t\tif exist {\n\t\t\treturn true, nil\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\treturn false, nil\n}\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run, confirm PASS.**\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: gofmt + commit**\n\n```bash\ngofmt -w internal/store/retier.go internal/store/retier_test.go\ngit add internal/store/retier.go internal/store/retier_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(store): CrossTierLinks + WasPushed retier soft-gate queries\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 4: CLI — `retier` / `promote` / `share` / `private`\n\n**Files:** Modify `cmd/kref/commands.go` (add `runRetier`, `confirmRetier`, three commands), `cmd/kref/main.go` (register), `cmd/kref/cli_test.go` (append).\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Write the failing CLI tests** — append inside `Describe(\"kref CLI\", func() {...})` in `cmd/kref/cli_test.go`:\n\n```go\n\tIt(\"promote moves an entry to shared and retier records provenance\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"init\", \"--name\", \"T\", \"--email\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tout := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"add\", \"--tier\", \"personal\", \"--title\", \"Doc\", \"--body\", \"clean prose\", \"--json\")\n\t\tvar added struct {\n\t\t\tID string `json:\"id\"`\n\t\t}\n\t\tExpect(json.Unmarshal([]byte(out), \u0026added)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tExpect(run(\"--dir\", dir, \"promote\", \"--yes\", added.ID)).To(ContainSubstring(\"shared\"))\n\t\tshow := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"show\", added.ID, \"--json\")\n\t\tExpect(show).To(ContainSubstring(`\"tier\": \"shared\"`))\n\t\tExpect(show).To(ContainSubstring(`\"trigger\": \"retier\"`))\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"private demotes an entry to the private tier\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"init\", \"--name\", \"T\", \"--email\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tout := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"add\", \"--tier\", \"personal\", \"--title\", \"Doc\", \"--body\", \"b\", \"--json\")\n\t\tvar added struct {\n\t\t\tID string `json:\"id\"`\n\t\t}\n\t\tExpect(json.Unmarshal([]byte(out), \u0026added)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tExpect(run(\"--dir\", dir, \"private\", added.ID)).To(ContainSubstring(\"private\"))\n\t\tExpect(run(\"--dir\", dir, \"show\", added.ID, \"--json\")).To(ContainSubstring(`\"tier\": \"private\"`))\n\t})\n\n\tIt(\"promote of a secret-bearing entry is blocked\", func() {\n\t\tdir := gitRepo()\n\t\trun(\"--dir\", dir, \"init\", \"--name\", \"T\", \"--email\", \"t@e.com\")\n\t\tout := run(\"--dir\", dir, \"add\", \"--tier\", \"personal\", \"--title\", \"Leaky\", \"--body\", \"AKIALALEMEL33243OLIA\", \"--json\")\n\t\tvar added struct {\n\t\t\tID string `json:\"id\"`\n\t\t}\n\t\tExpect(json.Unmarshal([]byte(out), \u0026added)).To(Succeed())\n\n\t\tcmd := newRootCmd()\n\t\tvar b bytes.Buffer\n\t\tcmd.SetOut(\u0026b)\n\t\tcmd.SetErr(\u0026b)\n\t\tcmd.SetArgs([]string{\"--dir\", dir, \"promote\", \"--yes\", added.ID})\n\t\terr := cmd.Execute()\n\t\tExpect(err).To(HaveOccurred())\n\t\tExpect(err.Error()).To(ContainSubstring(\"promote blocked\"))\n\t\tExpect(err.Error()).NotTo(ContainSubstring(\"AKIALALEMEL33243OLIA\"))\n\t\t// Not moved.\n\t\tExpect(run(\"--dir\", dir, \"show\", added.ID, \"--json\")).To(ContainSubstring(`\"tier\": \"personal\"`))\n\t})\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: Run, confirm FAIL** — unknown command `promote` / `private`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 3: Implement the CLI** — in `cmd/kref/commands.go`, add the helper, the confirm prompt, and the three commands:\n\n```go\n// confirmRetier asks for an interactive \"yes\" before promoting to shared.\nfunc confirmRetier(cmd *cobra.Command, snap *entry.Snapshot) (bool, error) {\n\tout := cmd.ErrOrStderr()\n\tfmt.Fprintf(out, \"Promote %s (%q) to the shared tier? It becomes visible to everyone you sync with.\\n\", render.ShortID(snap.ID), snap.Title)\n\tfmt.Fprint(out, \"Type 'yes' to proceed: \")\n\tline, err := bufio.NewReader(cmd.InOrStdin()).ReadString('\\n')\n\tif err != nil \u0026\u0026 err != io.EOF {\n\t\treturn false, err\n\t}\n\treturn strings.TrimSpace(line) == \"yes\", nil\n}\n\nfunc runRetier(cmd *cobra.Command, dir, idArg, tierArg string, yes bool) error {\n\ttarget, err := parseTier(tierArg)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\ts, err := store.Open(dir)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\tdefer s.Close()\n\tid, err := resolveArg(s, idArg)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\tsnap, err := s.Get(id)\n\tif err != nil {\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\tfrom := snap.Tier\n\tif from == string(target) {\n\t\treturn emit(cmd,\n\t\t\tfunc(w io.Writer, _ bool) { fmt.Fprintf(w, \"%s already in %s\\n\", render.ShortID(id), target) },\n\t\t\tmap[string]string{\"status\": \"noop\", \"id\": id.String(), \"tier\": string(target)})\n\t}\n\tout := cmd.ErrOrStderr()\n\tif target == entry.TierShared {\n\t\tdangling, err := s.CrossTierLinks(id, target)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t}\n\t\tfor _, l := range dangling {\n\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(out, \"warning: links to %s (%q), which stays below shared — teammates won't see it\\n\", render.ShortID(l.ID), l.Title)\n\t\t}\n\t\tif !yes {\n\t\t\tconfirmed, err := confirmRetier(cmd, snap)\n\t\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t\tif !confirmed {\n\t\t\t\treturn emit(cmd,\n\t\t\t\t\tfunc(w io.Writer, _ bool) { fmt.Fprintf(w, \"aborted %s\\n\", render.ShortID(id)) },\n\t\t\t\t\tmap[string]string{\"status\": \"aborted\", \"id\": id.String()})\n\t\t\t}\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tif from == string(entry.TierShared) \u0026\u0026 target != entry.TierShared {\n\t\tpushed, err := s.WasPushed(id)\n\t\tif err != nil {\n\t\t\treturn err\n\t\t}\n\t\tif pushed {\n\t\t\tfmt.Fprintf(out, \"warning: %s was already pushed; demoting only stops FUTURE local sync — rotate if sensitive, it cannot retract what already left\\n\", render.ShortID(id))\n\t\t}\n\t}\n\tactor, actorKind := resolveActor(cmd, s)\n\tif err := s.Retier(id, target, actor, actorKind); err != nil {\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\treturn emit(cmd,\n\t\tfunc(w io.Writer, _ bool) { fmt.Fprintf(w, \"retiered %s: %s → %s\\n\", render.ShortID(id), from, target) },\n\t\tmap[string]string{\"status\": \"retiered\", \"id\": id.String(), \"from\": from, \"to\": string(target)})\n}\n\nfunc newRetierCmd(dir *string) *cobra.Command {\n\tvar yes bool\n\tc := \u0026cobra.Command{\n\t\tUse:   \"retier \u003cid|path\u003e \u003ctier\u003e\",\n\t\tShort: \"Move an entry to a visibility tier (private|personal|shared)\",\n\t\tArgs:  cobra.ExactArgs(2),\n\t\tRunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\n\t\t\treturn runRetier(cmd, *dir, args[0], args[1], yes)\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\tc.Flags().BoolVar(\u0026yes, \"yes\", false, \"skip the promote-to-shared confirmation prompt\")\n\treturn c\n}\n\nfunc newPromoteCmd(dir *string) *cobra.Command {\n\tvar yes bool\n\tc := \u0026cobra.Command{\n\t\tUse:     \"promote \u003cid|path\u003e\",\n\t\tAliases: []string{\"share\"},\n\t\tShort:   \"Promote an entry to the shared tier\",\n\t\tArgs:    cobra.ExactArgs(1),\n\t\tRunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\n\t\t\treturn runRetier(cmd, *dir, args[0], string(entry.TierShared), yes)\n\t\t},\n\t}\n\tc.Flags().BoolVar(\u0026yes, \"yes\", false, \"skip the confirmation prompt\")\n\treturn c\n}\n\nfunc newPrivateCmd(dir *string) *cobra.Command {\n\treturn \u0026cobra.Command{\n\t\tUse:   \"private \u003cid|path\u003e\",\n\t\tShort: \"Demote an entry to the private tier (panic button)\",\n\t\tArgs:  cobra.ExactArgs(1),\n\t\tRunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {\n\t\t\treturn runRetier(cmd, *dir, args[0], string(entry.TierPrivate), true)\n\t\t},\n\t}\n}\n```\n\n(`bufio`, `io`, `strings`, `fmt`, `entry`, `render`, `store` are already imported in `commands.go`.)\n\nIn `cmd/kref/main.go`, register in the lifecycle group after `newSupersedeCmd`:\n\n```go\n\taddTo(\"lifecycle\", newRetierCmd(\u0026dir))\n\taddTo(\"lifecycle\", newPromoteCmd(\u0026dir))\n\taddTo(\"lifecycle\", newPrivateCmd(\u0026dir))\n```\n\n- [ ] **Step 4: Run CLI tests, confirm PASS** — `KREF_GITLEAKS=$(pwd)/bin/gitleaks GOTOOLCHAIN=auto go test ./cmd/kref/...` → PASS.\n\n- [ ] **Step 5: gofmt + commit**\n\n```bash\ngofmt -w cmd/kref/commands.go cmd/kref/main.go cmd/kref/cli_test.go\ngit add cmd/kref/commands.go cmd/kref/main.go cmd/kref/cli_test.go\ngit commit -m \"feat(cli): kref retier/promote/share/private with gates\"\n```\n\n---\n\n## Task 5: Documentation\n\n**Files:** Modify `internal/entry/snapshot.go` (trigger doc), `README.md`, `CHANGELOG.md`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 1: Update the trigger doc comment** — in `internal/entry/snapshot.go`, the `OriginEvent.Trigger` field comment reads `// create | ingest`; change it to `// create | ingest | retier`.\n\n- [ ] **Step 2: README** — in the command reference fenced block, after the `kref supersede \u003cold\u003e \u003cnew\u003e` line add:\n\n```\nkref retier \u003cid|path\u003e \u003ctier\u003e [--yes]          move to a tier: private|personal|shared\nkref promote \u003cid|path\u003e [--yes]                promote to shared (share is an alias)\nkref private \u003cid|path\u003e                        demote to private (panic button)\n```\n\nIn the `### Hygiene \u0026 consolidation` or `### Entries and tiers` concept area (pick the tiers concept — search for \"visibility tier\"), add a short paragraph:\n\n```markdown\n**Retiering keeps identity.** `kref retier \u003cid\u003e \u003ctier\u003e` (and the 